# .trivyignore
#
# List CVE IDs here ONLY when you've deliberately assessed the risk and
# decided to accept it (e.g. a vulnerability in a code path you don't use,
# or one with no available fix yet and low real-world exploitability).
#
# Never add entries here just to make a scan pass - that defeats the point
# of scanning in the first place. Each entry should have a comment explaining
# why it's accepted and by whom, e.g.:
#
# CVE-2023-XXXXX  # Accepted 2026-07-16 by <name> - unused code path, no fix available yet
